#: src/qml/Settings/PlaybackSettings.qml:107
msgctxt "@label"
msgid "Hardware decoding"
msgstr "Descodificación por soporte físico"

#: src/qml/Settings/PlaybackSettings.qml:149
#, fuzzy
#| msgctxt "@info:tooltip hardware decoding setting"
#| msgid ""
#| "Specify the hardware video decoding API that should be used if possible. "
#| "Whether hardware decoding is actually done depends on the video codec. If "
#| "hardware decoding is not possible, mpv will fall back on software "
#| "decoding.<br><br><ul><li><strong>auto</strong> tries to automatically "
#| "enable hardware decoding using the first available method.</"
#| "li><li><strong>auto-safe</strong> similar to auto, but allows only "
#| "whitelisted methods that are considered \"safe\".</li><li><strong>vaapi</"
#| "strong> works with Intel and AMD GPUs only. It also requires the opengl "
#| "EGL backend.</li><li><strong>nvdec</strong> the newest, and recommended "
#| "method to do hardware decoding on Nvidia GPUs.</li><li><strong>cuda</"
#| "strong> an older implementation of hardware decoding on Nvidia GPUs.</"
#| "li><li><strong>videotoolbox</strong></li><li><strong>d3d11va</strong></"
#| "li></ul><br><br>You can read more about hardware decoding here: <a "
#| "href='https://mpv.io/manual/stable/#options-hwdec'>https://mpv.io/manual/"
#| "stable/#options-hwdec</a><br><br>You can set another hardware decoder by "
#| "creating a startup custom command <strong>set hwdec <i>decoder_name</i></"
#| "strong>."
msgctxt "@info:tooltip hardware decoding setting"
msgid ""
"Specify the hardware video decoding API that should be used if possible. "
"Whether hardware decoding is actually done depends on the video codec. If "
"hardware decoding is not possible, mpv will fall back on software decoding."
"<br><br><ul><li><strong>auto</strong> tries to automatically enable hardware "
"decoding using the first available method.</li><li><strong>auto-safe</"
"strong> similar to auto, but allows only whitelisted methods that are "
"considered “safe”.</li><li><strong>vaapi</strong> works with Intel and AMD "
"GPUs only. It also requires the opengl EGL backend.</li><li><strong>nvdec</"
"strong> the newest, and recommended method to do hardware decoding on Nvidia "
"GPUs.</li><li><strong>cuda</strong> an older implementation of hardware "
"decoding on Nvidia GPUs.</li><li><strong>videotoolbox</strong></"
"li><li><strong>d3d11va</strong></li></ul><br><br>You can read more about "
"hardware decoding here: <a href='https://mpv.io/manual/stable/#options-"
"hwdec'>https://mpv.io/manual/stable/#options-hwdec</a><br><br>You can set "
"another hardware decoder by creating a startup custom command <strong>set "
"hwdec <i>decoder_name</i></strong>."
msgstr ""
"Indique a API de descodificación de vídeo mediante soporte físico que "
"debería usarse cando sexa posíbel. Se a descodificación mediante soporte "
"físico se usa de verdade ou non depende do códec de vídeo. Se non se pode "
"descodificar mediante soporte físico, farase mediante soporte lóxico."
"<br><br><ul><li><strong>auto</strong> intenta activar a descodificación "
"mediante soporte físico automaticamente co primeiro método dispoñíbel.</"
"li><li><strong>auto-safe</strong> é semellante a «auto», pero só permite os "
"métodos da lista de permitidos que se consideran “seguros”.</"
"li><li><strong>vaapi</strong> só funciona coas GPU de Intel e de AMD. Tamén "
"require o motor EGL de OpenGL.</li><li><strong>nvdec</strong> é o método "
"actual e recomendado de descodificación mediante soporte físico con GPU de "
"Nvidia.</li><li><strong>cuda</strong> é unha versión anterior de "
"descodificación mediante soporte físico con GPU de Nvidia.</"
"li><li><strong>videotoolbox</strong></li><li><strong>d3d11va</strong></li></"
"ul><br><br>Para máis información sobre descodificación mediante soporte "
"físico, consulte: <a href='https://mpv.io/manual/stable/#options-"
"hwdec'>https://mpv.io/manual/stable/#options-hwdec</a> (en "
"inglés)<br><br>Para definir outro descodificador mediante soporte físico, "
"cree unha orde personalizada de inicio <strong>set hwdec <i>decoder_name</"
"i></strong>."

